WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:12.000
When every delegated task gets the premium lane, the policy can disappear. Mars Cost Router makes the decision explicit, bounded, and reviewable.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:27.000
Mars Cost Router is an independent, instruction-driven delegation policy for Codex. Mars is our project brand, not a model. This project is unofficial and not affiliated with or endorsed by OpenAI.

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:43.000
Three lanes guide the policy: Economy for bounded inspection; Balanced for focused implementation, tests, and review; Premium for risk, uncertainty, security boundaries, or difficult debugging.

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:58.000
Add the marketplace repository, add the named plugin, and start a new Codex session. Open it in the plugin browser or at-sign surface; where skills are exposed, use the Mars Cost Router skill syntax.

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:18.000
There is no hidden runtime hook. The skill guides the root agent, which writes the bounded child request with an explicit model, reasoning effort, and no inherited turns. The root owns scope, integration, and final verification.

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:34.000
The requested payload has a generic task name, self-contained message, selected model and effort, and fork turns set to none. It is not proof of the child’s effective route.

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:50.000
In a fixed read-only series, the selective Terra and Sol policy and all-Sol high baseline each passed twelve of twelve deterministic checks, with zero observed retries and reroutes.

00:01:50.000 --> 00:02:06.000
Child-token totals were nearly flat: 356,116 versus 356,494, minus 0.11% recorded. Most recorded total difference occurred at the root. Total tokens and median wall time are neutral observations, not savings or quality claims.

00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:13.000
The series is order- and cache-confounded. It does not prove causality, general quality, billing outcomes, or effective routing.

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:20.000
Choose by risk and effort, keep child tasks bounded, and verify at the root. Read the policy, evidence, and privacy notes.
